def is_prime(n: int) -> bool:
    if n < 2:
        return False
    if n < 4:
        return True
    if n % 2 == 0 or n % 3 == 0:
        return False
    i = 5
    while i * i <= n:
        if n % i == 0 or n % (i + 2) == 0:
            return False
        i += 6
    return True
```
This function uses trial division with the 6k +/- 1 optimization, giving O(sqrt(n)) time complexity.

